                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Feb. 14: State-run mining major NMDC is likely to file a revised set of papers for its follow-on public offer with Sebi this week after incorporating the market regulators comments on its draft prospectus submitted last month. NMDC is expecting Sebis comments on the draft prospectus on Monday. The company will incorporate the comments and file the red herring prospectus to the regulator later this week, a finance ministry official said.                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 14: The National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority has eased norms for the pricing of imported drugs, allowing companies to seek approval once in six months.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 14: The government is looking at the option of allowing BSNL to buy part of the originally planned 93 million lines with a moderate hike in cost to boost its network.                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 14: Corporate Indias confidence in the management of economic policies by the Centre has taken a severe beating, despite several indicators that point to a turnaround in the economy, according to a survey by economic think tank NCAER and MasterCard.                                                                                                                          
